  • Method Details

    • getCodeForIndex

      public String getCodeForIndex()
      Returns the subfield code needed for Solr indexing. If MQ or BIBFRAME tags are defined, they are used in that order. Otherwise, the code is prefixed with an underscore (and special characters are replaced with their names). Note: The code that's referred to here is the identifier of the subfield and not code in the sense of possible values of the subfield.
      Returns:
      The subfield code for Solr indexing.

    • resolve

      public String resolve(String value)
      Resolves the value of a subfield to its label if it can be found in the codeList or the list of codes. Otherwise, it returns the value as is.
      Parameters:
      value - The value of the subfield to resolve.
      Returns:
      The resolved value. Either the label of the code or the value itself.
